No, No, No, No, No, brief (1-3 elements), Patient following up on STD results complains of a discharge accompanied with burning with urination., Home, Home, 5:46 PM, Doxy.me, Contraception management - New ·Instructions: Your prescription was sent to the pharmacy
You may start your birth control pill today
Take one tablet of your birth control at the same time every day. If you do not take it around the same time every day, you CAN get pregnant.
If either re-starting or just starting your birth control, use a condom for the first 7 days. Consistent condom use is best, as your birth control pills do NOT protect against sexually transmitted infection, Std screening - Comment Only ·Instructions: Come to the clinic for repeat STI and urine testing today
Use a condom with EVERY sexual encounter to minimize your risk for sexually transmitted infection and unplanned pregnancy, brief (1-3 elements), " This is a phone conversation in lieu of in-office visit due to the coronavirus emergency."
Nyla Hodge is a 18 Years Old Female ( DOB 01/19/2002) to follow up on urinary symptoms. Notes occas burning with urination X 7d. Symptoms similar to last telehealth check. NO frequency, no fevers, no hematuria. Denies vaginal discharge no itching no odor. Using scented bath soap, occas using DOVE
Currently sexually active with one male parnter X 8 months. No recent intercourse. Occas condoms Hx CT 12/2019, pt was treated, was with other partner at time, states her current partner was not treated but tested negative
Denies health problems, no clotting disorders, no hospitalization
Was on OCP. Occas notes late taking a bit late. Will consider LARC in future. Does not desire pregnancy, high school senior, has college plans for fall LMP 5/3/2020
Pt reported weight 115, non smoker

REports no discharge that is unusual. No abd pain. DYsuria is "Splash dysuria." NO itching. LAst intercourse was about a month ago. reports using concdoms then. reports sheltering in place
